flowRoot.flowPara: If et is positive and |et| is large enough,
a value may change (0→1), or stay (1→1).
-- i.e. it can make False into True, but
If et is negative and |et| is large enough,
a value may change (1→0), or stay (0→0).
-- i.e. it can make True into False, but
If |et| is small, it has no effect (0→0, 1→1)
Since the same word does not always make changes, we should look at several appearances of the word in the dataset to determine the binary effect (add, del or no effect)
